str2: A primary particle; but, and, etc.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To hear, listen, comprehend by hearing; pass: is heard, reported. A primary verb; to hear.
And, even, also, namely.
Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: (a) I make, manufacture, construct, (b) I do, act, cause. Apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary; to make or do.

parse: Verb - Present Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
Like, similar to, resembling, of equal rank. From the base of homou; similar.
A man, one of the human race. From aner and ops; man-faced, i.e. A human being.

parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Dative Masculine Singular
str2: From the same as oikodome; to be a house-builder, i.e. Construct or confirm.
From oikos; properly, residence, but usually an abode; by implication, a family.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Contracted from a primary word; soil; by extension a region, or the solid part or the whole of the terrene globe.
Apart from, separately from; without. Adverb from chora; at a space, i.e. Separately or apart from.
From a derivative of tithemi; something put down, i.e. A substruction.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
A river, torrent, stream. Probably from a derivative of the alternate of pino; a current, brook or freshet, i.e. Running water.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To dash against, as waves. From pros and rhegnumi; to tear towards, i.e. Burst upon.

parse: Personal / Relative Pronoun - Dative Feminine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, that.
And, even, also, namely.
Immediately, soon, at once. Adverb from euthus; directly, i.e. At once or soon.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A reduplicated and contracted form of peto; probably akin to petomai through the idea of alighting; to fall.
And, even, also, namely.
Large, great, in the widest sense.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
That, that one there, yonder. From ekei; that one (neuter) thing); often intensified by the article prefixed.
What is broken, a ruin. From rhegnumi; something torn, i.e. A fragment.
